<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> The <i>Gita Dhyanam</i> is a traditional short poem sometimes found as a prefatory to editions of the <i>Bhagavad Gita</i>. Verse 4 refers to all the Upanishads as the cows, and the Gita as the milk drawn from them. (<a href="#CITEREFChidbhavananda1997" title="">Chidbhavananda 1997</a>, pp.&#160;67–74)</li>
