<li id="cite_note-veg-115"><b><a href="#cite_ref-veg_115-0" title="">^</a></b> Surveys studying food habits of Indians include: <a href="http://www.fao.org/WAIRDOCS/LEAD/X6170E/x6170e09.htm#TopOfPage" class="external text" title="http://www.fao.org/WAIRDOCS/LEAD/X6170E/x6170e09.htm#TopOfPage" rel="nofollow">"Diary and poultry sector growth in India"</a>, <a href="http://www.fas.usda.gov/htp/highlights/2001/india.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.fas.usda.gov/htp/highlights/2001/india.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Indian consumer patterns"</a> and <a href="http://www.ers.usda.gov/amberwaves/February04/Features/ElephantJogs.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ers.usda.gov/amberwaves/February04/Features/ElephantJogs.htm" rel="nofollow">"Agri reform in India"</a>. Results indicate that Indians who eat meat do so infrequently with less than 30% consuming non-vegetarian foods regularly, although the reasons may be economical.</li>
