<li><cite id="CITEREFMonier-Williams1974"><a href="/wiki/Monier_Monier-Williams" title="Monier Monier-Williams">Monier-Williams, Monier</a> (1974), <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=U5IBXA4UpT0C&amp;dq=isbn:1421265311" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=U5IBXA4UpT0C&amp;dq=isbn:1421265311" rel="nofollow">Brahmanism and Hinduism: Or, Religious Thought and Life in India, as Based on the Veda and Other Sacred Books of the Hindus</a></i>, Adamant Media Corporation, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1421265311" class="internal">ISBN 1421265311</a><span class="printonly">, &lt;<a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=U5IBXA4UpT0C&amp;dq=isbn:1421265311" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=U5IBXA4UpT0C&amp;dq=isbn:1421265311" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=U5IBXA4UpT0C&amp;dq=isbn:1421265311</a>&gt;</span>. Retrieved on 2007-07-08</cite></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFMorgan1987">Morgan, Kenneth W., ed. (1987), written at Delhi, <i>The Religion of the Hindus</i> (New ed.), Motilal Banarsidas, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/8120803876" class="internal">ISBN 8120803876</a></cite></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFRenou1964">Renou, Louis (1964), <i>The Nature of Hinduism</i>, Walker</cite></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFRinehart2004">Rinehart, R (Ed.) (2004), <i>Contemporary Hinduism: Ritual, Culture, and Practice</i>, ABC-Clio, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1576079058" class="internal">ISBN 1-57607-905-8</a></cite></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFWeightman1998">Weightman, Simon (1998), "Hinduism", in Hinnells, John (Ed.), <i>The new Penguin handbook of living religions</i>, <a href="/wiki/Penguin_books" title="Penguin books" class="mw-redirect">Penguin books</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0140514805" class="internal">ISBN 0-140-51480-5</a></cite></li>
